</li><li tabindex="0" spellcheck="false" data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-xiLah cpQDEO pf-984_">The Patient Safety Watch report highlights some stark statistics. When looking at rates of treatable deaths (those which can be mainly avoided through timely and effective healthcare intervention), if the UK matched the top decile of OECD countries, this would equate to 12,675 fewer deaths per year – that is 243 fewer deaths every week.
